Best Solution: Use Slick Carousel (Lightweight & Responsive)
https://kenwheeler.github.io/slick/

Steps to Implement:
1. Add slick css & js cdn in your layout
html
Copy code
<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/slick-carousel@1.8.1/slick/slick.css" />
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/slick-carousel@1.8.1/slick/slick.min.js"></script>
2. Update your structure like this:
html
Copy code
<div class="category-content" id="kotcard">
    <div class="card-slider">
        @foreach (var order in Model)
        {
            <div class="card-container">
                // your card content here
            </div>
        }
    </div>
</div>
3. Initialize slick in JS after ajax success (important)
javascript
Copy code
success: function (data) {
    $('#kotcard').html(data);

    $('.card-slider').slick({
        slidesToShow: 3,   // desktop
        slidesToScroll: 1,
        prevArrow: $('.prev-btn'),
        nextArrow: $('.next-btn'),
        responsive: [
            {
                breakpoint: 1024,
                settings: {
                    slidesToShow: 2
                }
            },
            {
                breakpoint: 600,
                settings: {
                    slidesToShow: 1
                }
            }
        ]
    });
}
4. Update your buttons like:
html
Copy code
<button class="btn pagination-btn prev-btn">
    <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-left"></i>
</button>

<button class="btn pagination-btn next-btn">
    <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-right"></i>
</button>
